
WSPR manpages are build using AsciiDoc (a2x). You do not need LaTex, DocBook,
A-A-P etc,

REQUIEMENTS
-----------
* Python	(installed on most *Nix systems)
* xslproc	(in most repo inventories)
* AsciiDoc

DOWNLOAD
--------
* http://iweb.dl.sourceforge.net/project/asciidoc/asciidoc/8.6.9/asciidoc-8.6.9.tar.gz


INSTALL XSL
-----------
* sudo apt-get install xslproc
* mkdir ~/bin <== can be anywhere really
* cd ~/bin and untart AsciiDoc
* Add the following to ~/bashrc:
* PATH=~/path/to/install/asciidoc:~/bin:$PATH <== path to where you co ../branches/doc/.. ..

UPDATE BASHRC
-------------
* export $PATH
* source ~/.bashrc && source ~/.profile <== or logout / back in


LINK ASCIIDOC to BIN
--------------------
* cd ~/bin
- ln -s ~/path/to/install/asciidoc.py ./asciidoc
- ln -s ~/path/to/install/asciidoc/a2x.py ./a2x


BUILD MANPAGES
--------------
* cd ~/wspr/doc/man1/wsjtx.1.txt .
* a2x --doctype manpage --format manpage --no-xmllint wspr.1.txt


READ MANPAGES
-------------
man wsjtx.1

